    "narrative": "The offensive outlook for LawDog today centers on **Tyler Freeman**, who stands as our clear-cut priority start with a 67.69 efficiency score. The matchup against Randy V\u00e1squez (5.43 xERA) is the catalyst here; V\u00e1squez\u2019s struggles against right-handed hitters combined with an assumed #2 slot in the lineup maximize **Tyler Freeman**'s run-scoring potential. While **Gleyber Torres** (51.30) and **Gavin Sheets** (47.35) provide moderate floor support, they are facing sturdier arms in Jimmy Herget and Abel, respectively. **Geraldo Perdomo** remains a marginal start at 41.97, as he deals with a tough matchup against McLean (3.04 xERA), forcing him to rely heavily on his contact skills rather than raw power to avoid a sub-40 bench threshold.\n\nRegarding bench composition, the decision-making process was relatively straightforward today due to several key assets being off the field. With **Jos\u00e9 Ram\u00edrez**, **Cal Raleigh**, and **Will Smith** all inactive, our bench depth is essentially non-existent. **Lawrence Butler** was the only potential consideration, but he was relegated to the pine due to a difficult matchup against Weathers and an apparent lack of a confirmed path to playing time. Looking ahead, we need to monitor the health and usage of **Bryson Stott**, **Daulton Varsho**, **Taylor Ward**, **Yainer Diaz**, **Jonathan Aranda**, **Matt Chapman**, **Wenceel Perez**, **Luis Arraez**, **Masyn Winn**, **Brendan Donovan**, **Jung Hoo Lee**, **Jeremiah Jackson**, and **Drew Gilbert** to ensure we don't bleed games against our cap, particularly as we hunt for stolen bases to bridge the gap in our 5x5 standing. No significant weather risks are currently flagged for our active starters, though we are operating under \"Lineup Pending\" assumptions for both **Gavin Sheets** and **Tyler Freeman**, which necessitates a final check before first pitch to ensure they aren't rested.",
